This has since pushed up Malawi's per capita fish consumption, reaching 12.63 kg per person per year, from 12.47 kg per person per year in 2017, which is closer to the 13 to 15kg recommended by World Health Organisation.  

Statistics also indicate rising fish volumes and prices pushed up earnings by 11.23%. 

George Mhango reports from Blantyre in Malawi.. --ChannelAfrica--